, "unit": null, "marks": 14, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Write Short notes on the following:\\na) Bulk Modulus\\nb) Elastic Curve\\nc) Principal Strain\\nd) Middle-Third Rule", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": null, "unit": null, "marks": 14, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": "A diagram showing three vertical rods supporting a horizontal beam which carries a downward load W=50 kN. The central rod is labeled 'Steel' and has a length of '3m'. The two outer rods are labeled 'Copper' and each has a length of '2m'. All rods are shown with a diameter of 25mm (implied from text). The top ends of the rods are fixed to a rigid support, and the bottom ends are connected to a horizontal beam. The load W=50 kN is applied at the center of the horizontal beam.", "question_text": "Two copper rods and one steel rod lie in a vertical plane and together support a load of 50 kN as shown in figure. Each rod is 25 mm in diameter, length of steel rod is 3 m and length of each copper rod is 2m. If modulus of elasticity of steel is twice that of copper, determine the stress in each rod.", "image_strategy": "CANVAS", "recreated_image_url": "https://s3.us-east-005.backblazeb2.com/campusprep/recreated/37c5213c-e85e-41ce-af20-ac75d9aad5c6.png?X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&X-Amz-Credential=005ff988bd983190000000001%2F20260225%2Fus-east-005%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&X-Amz-Date=20260225T191859Z&X-Amz-Expires=3600&X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&X-Amz-Signature=880a2ca4c9399e56439bf91ee104c7497b011a507b19cfa3e6aaa24ad4f429dd", "recreated_html_source": "<canvas id=\\"canvas\\"></canvas>\\n<script>\\n(function() {\\n  const canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');\\n  const dpr = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;\\n  const logicalWidth = 600;\\n  const logicalHeight = 400;\\n  canvas.style.width = logicalWidth + 'px';\\n  canvas.style.height = logicalHeight + 'px';\\n  canvas.width = logicalWidth * dpr;\\n  canvas.height = logicalHeight * dpr;\\n  const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\\n  ctx.scale(dpr, dpr);\\n  ctx.font = '14px Arial';\\n  ctx.textAlign = 'center';\\n  ctx.textBaseline = 'middle';\\n  \\n  // Colors\\n  const slate = '#708090';\\n  const indigo = '#4B0082';\\n  const emerald = '#50C878';\\n  const black = '#000000';\\n  \\n  // Geometry\\n  const supportY = 80;          // y‑position of rigid support line\\n  const beamY = 260;            // y‑position of horizontal beam\\n  const rodX = [150, 300, 450]; // x‑positions of the three rods\\n  const rodLengths = [2, 3, 2]; // meters (outer, centre, outer)\\n  const scale = 60;             // 60 px per metre\\n  const rodDiameter = 25;       // mm (only shown as text)\\n  \\n  // Draw rigid support\\n  ctx.strokeStyle = slate;\\n  ctx.lineWidth = 6;\\n  ctx.beginPath();\\n  ctx.moveTo(100, supportY);\\n  ctx.lineTo(500, supportY);\\n  ctx.stroke();\\n  \\n  // Draw vertical rods\\n  ctx.strokeStyle = indigo;\\n  ctx.lineWidth = 4;\\n  for (let i = 0; i < 3; i++) {\\n    const x = rodX[i];\\n    const lengthM = rodLengths[i];\\n    const topY = supportY + (3 - lengthM) * scale; // outer rods start lower\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(x, topY);\\n    ctx.lineTo(x, beamY);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n    \\n    // Label each rod\\n    ctx.fillStyle = black;\\n    const label = (i===1 ? 'Steel' : 'Copper') + '\\\\n' + lengthM + ' m\\\\nØ' + rodDiameter + ' mm';\\n    const lines = label.split('\\\\n');\\n    for (let j = 0; j < lines.length; j++) {\\n      ctx.fillText(lines[j], x, topY - 30 - j*16);\\n    }\\n  }\\n  \\n  // Draw horizontal beam\\n  ctx.strokeStyle = emerald;\\n  ctx.lineWidth = 5;\\n  ctx.beginPath();\\n  ctx.moveTo(rodX[0], beamY);\\n  ctx.lineTo(rodX[2], beamY);\\n  ctx.stroke();\\n  \\n  // Draw load arrow\\n  const arrowX = (rodX[0] + rodX[2]) / 2;\\n  const arrowTop = beamY - 20;\\n  const arrowBottom = beamY + 80;\\n  ctx.strokeStyle = black;\\n  ctx.fillStyle = black;\\n  ctx.lineWidth = 2;\\n  // shaft\\n  ctx.beginPath();\\n  ctx.moveTo(arrowX, arrowTop);\\n  ctx.lineTo(arrowX, arrowBottom);\\n  ctx.stroke();\\n  // head\\n  ctx.beginPath();\\n  ctx.moveTo(arrowX - 10, arrowBottom - 15);\\n  ctx.lineTo(arrowX, arrowBottom);\\n  ctx.lineTo(arrowX + 10, arrowBottom - 15);\\n  ctx.closePath();\\n  ctx.fill();\\n  // label\\n  ctx.fillText('W = 50 kN', arrowX, arrowBottom + 20);\\n  \\n  // Optional: dimension lines for rod lengths (vertical)\\n  ctx.strokeStyle = black;\\n  ctx.lineWidth = 1;\\n  ctx.setLineDash([4,2]);\\n  for (let i = 0; i < 3; i++) {\\n    const x = rodX[i];\\n    const lengthM = rodLengths[i];\\n    const topY = supportY + (3 - lengthM) * scale;\\n    // dimension line\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(x - 15, topY);\\n    ctx.lineTo(x - 15, beamY);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n    // arrows\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(x - 20, topY);\\n    ctx.lineTo(x - 15, topY - 5);\\n    ctx.lineTo(x - 10, topY);\\n    ctx.moveTo(x - 20, beamY);\\n    ctx.lineTo(x - 15, beamY + 5);\\n    ctx.lineTo(x - 10, beamY);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n    // text\\n    ctx.fillStyle = black;\\n    ctx.fillText(lengthM + ' m', x - 30, (topY + beamY)/2);\\n  }\\n  ctx.setLineDash([]);\\n})();\\n</script>"}, {"part": null, "unit": null, "marks": 14, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "A simply supported beam of 5m span carries a uniformly distributed load of 10 kN per metre run and a point load of 10 kN at 2m from left support. Determine the magnitude and location of the peak bending moment. Proceed to determine suitable section of this beam if the maximum allowable stress is limited to 8 N/mm$^2$. Take depth twice the width.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": null, "unit": null, "marks": 14, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "A shaft is subjected to a max. torque of 10 kN-m and bending moment 7.5 kN-m at a particular section. If the allowable equivalent stress in simple tension is 160 mN/m$^2$. Determine the diameter of the shaft according 