nd Simpson's rule for area calculation.", "question_text": "Write notes on the following with neat sketch:\\ni) Mid ordinate rule\\nii) Average ordinate rule\\niii) Trapezoidal rule\\niv) Simpson's rule", "image_strategy": "GEN_PROMPT"}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Explain concurrent and non-concurrent co-planer forces in details.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": "Shear force and bending moment diagram for a simply supported beam with a uniformly distributed load of 10 KN/m and a point load of 20 KN at the center, with a span of 5m.", "question_text": "Draw the shear force and bending moment diagram for simply supported beam, which carries a uniformly distributed load of $10\\\\text{KN/m}$ and a point load of $20\\\\text{KN}$ on its center having span of $5\\\\text{m}$.", "image_strategy": "GEN_PROMPT"}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Define any two-laboratory test, those are conducted on bricks and cement.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "List out the various stages for the construction of a building and list out the various building materials used in construction works with brief details.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Discuss plastering and pointing in Civil Engineering construction works.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Define the method of joints and method of section to analyze a plane truss with a suitable example.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Define the following terms with respect to concrete:\\ni) Workability\\nii) Segregation", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": "A T-shaped plane lamina. The horizontal top bar is 80 mm wide and 20 mm high. The vertical stem is 20 mm wide and 65 mm high. The stem is centered under the horizontal bar. The diagram shows dimensions: top bar 80mm width, 20mm height. Stem 20mm width, 65mm height. The stem is centrally aligned with the top bar.", "question_text": "Determine the moment of inertia of the given plane lamina about its centroidal axis as shown in the figure below.", "image_strategy": "CANVAS", "recreated_image_url": "https://s3.us-east-005.backblazeb2.com/campusprep/recreated/36724725-51eb-4300-bd31-6405f351c726.png?X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&X-Amz-Credential=005ff988bd983190000000001%2F20260225%2Fus-east-005%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&X-Amz-Date=20260225T191805Z&X-Amz-Expires=3600&X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&X-Amz-Signature=9c13eab26d8e7591ef21ccc42f80d3a57dd2a8bd6176e3e5079550cd7905a2cc", "recreated_html_source": "<canvas id=\\"canvas\\"></canvas>\\n<script>\\nconst canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');\\nconst ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\\n\\n// logical dimensions (mm)\\nconst topWidth = 80;\\nconst topHeight = 20;\\nconst stemWidth = 20;\\nconst stemHeight = 65;\\nconst totalWidth = topWidth;\\nconst totalHeight = topHeight + stemHeight;\\n\\n// margins around the drawing (logical units)\\nconst margin = 10;\\n\\n// set canvas size (pixel units) – you can change these values\\ncanvas.width = 500;\\ncanvas.height = 500;\\ncanvas.style.width = '100%';\\ncanvas.style.height = 'auto';\\ncanvas.style.display = 'block';\\ncanvas.style.maxWidth = '600px';\\ncanvas.style.margin = '0 auto';\\ncanvas.style.background = '#fafafa';\\n\\n// compute scaling factor to fit drawing + margins into canvas\\nconst scaleX = canvas.width / (totalWidth + 2 * margin);\\nconst scaleY = canvas.height / (totalHeight + 2 * margin);\\nconst scale = Math.min(scaleX, scaleY);\\n\\n// translate to centre and apply scale\\nctx.translate((canvas.width - (totalWidth * scale)) / 2, (canvas.height - (totalHeight * scale)) / 2);\\nctx.scale(scale, scale);\\n\\n// helper to draw double‑headed dimension line with arrows\\nfunction drawDimension(x1, y1, x2, y2, offset, label) {\\n    const dx = x2 - x1;\\n    const dy = y2 - y1;\\n    const len = Math.hypot(dx, dy);\\n    const ux = dx / len;\\n    const uy = dy / len;\\n    const nx = -uy; // normal (perpendicular) unit vector\\n    const ny = ux;\\n\\n    // main dimension line (offset from the object)\\n    const ox1 = x1 + nx * offset;\\n    const oy1 = y1 + ny * offset;\\n    const ox2 = x2 + nx * offset;\\n    const oy2 = y2 + ny * offset;\\n\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = '#555';\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 0.4;\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(ox1, oy1);\\n    ctx.lineTo(ox2, oy2);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n\\n    // arrowheads\\n    const arrowSize = 2;\\n    function drawArrow(px, py, dirX, dirY) {\\n        ctx.beginPath();\\n        ctx.moveTo(px, py);\\n        ctx.lineTo(px - dirX * arrowSize + dirY * arrowSize * 0.5,\\n                   py - dirY * arrowSize - dirX * arrowSize * 0.5);\\n        ctx.lineTo(px - dirX * arrowSize - dirY * arrowSize * 0.5,\\n                   py - dirY * arrowSize + dirX * arrowSize * 0.5);\\n        ctx.closePath();\\n        ctx.fillStyle = '#555';\\n        ctx.fill();\\n    }\\n    drawArrow(ox1, oy1, -ux, -uy);\\n    drawArrow(ox2, oy2, ux, uy);\\n\\n    // extension lines from the object to the dimension line\\n    ctx.setLineDash([0.5, 0.5]);\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(x1, y1);\\n    ctx.lineTo(ox1, oy1);\\n    ctx.moveTo(x2, y2);\\n    ctx.lineTo(ox2, oy2);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n    ctx.setLineDash([]);\\n\\n    // label\\n    ctx.fillStyle = '#222';\\n    ctx.font = '3px sans-serif';\\n    ctx.textBaseline = 'middle';\\n    ctx.textAlign = 'center';\\n    const labelX = (ox1 + ox2) / 2;\\n    const labelY = (oy1 + oy2) / 2;\\n    ctx.save();\\n    ctx.translate(labelX, labelY);\\n    const angle = Math.atan2(dy, dx);\\n    ctx.rotate(angle);\\n    ctx.fillText(label, 0, -4);\\n    ctx.restore();\\n}\\n\\n// ---------- draw the T‑lamina ----------\\nctx.fillStyle = '#3b82f6'; // indigo for the solid\\nctx.strokeStyle = '#1e40af';\\nctx.lineWidth = 0.5;\\n\\n// top bar\\nctx.beginPath();\\nctx.rect(0, 0, topWidth, topHeight);\\nctx.fill();\\nctx.stroke();\\n\\n// stem (centered under the bar)\\nconst stemX = (topWidth - stemWidth) / 2;\\nctx.beginPath();\\nctx.rect(stemX, topHeight, stemWidth, stemHeight);\\nctx.fill();\\nctx.stroke();\\n\\n// ---------- dimensions ----------\\nconst dimOffset = 8; // distance of dimension line from the shape (logical units)\\n\\n// width of top bar\\ndrawDimension(0, -dimOffset, topWidth, -dimOffset, dimOffset, `${topWidth} mm`);\\n\\n// height of top bar\\ndrawDimension(-dimOffset, 0, -dimOffset, topHeight, dimOffset, `${topHeight} mm`);\\n\\n// stem width\\ndrawDimension(stemX, topHeight + stemHeight + dimOffset,\\n              stemX + stemWidth, topHeight + stemHeight + dimOffset,\\n              dimOffset, `${stemWidth} mm`);\\n\\n// stem height\\ndrawDimension(stemX + stemWidth + dimOffset,\\n              topHeight,\\n              stemX + stemWidth + dimOffset,\\n              topHeight + stemHeight,\\n              dimOffset, `${stemHeight} mm`);\\n</script>"}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Define the following terms:\\ni) True bearing and magnetic bearing\\nii) Fore sight and back sight\\niii) Local attraction\\niv) Errors in chain surveying", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "What do you understand by reversible and irreversible machines? Explain with suitable examples.", "image_strategy": null}]}	t	NATIVE	f	\N	2026-02-25 16:01:50.145513+00	2026-02-25 17:05:03.325669+00
