e": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Discuss the merits and demerits of Object-Oriented Methodology. Provide real-world scenarios where OOP is beneficial and where it may not be ideal.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Discuss the concepts of message passing in OOP. How", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "What are classes in OOP? Discuss how to identify classes. Create a class student with attributes like name, roll_number, and marks. Write methods to calculate the average marks and display student information. Demonstrate its use in a sample program.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Explain the concept of interfaces in OOP. How do interfaces differ from abstract classes? Discuss the use of both in software development.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Explain how interfaces in Object-Oriented Programming can facilitate polymorphism. Provide code examples to illustrate the use of interfaces in C++.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Discuss various data collections available in C++. How do these collections differ in terms of performance and use cases?", "image_strategy": null}]}	t	NATIVE	f	\N	2026-02-25 16:01:50.145638+00	2026-02-25 17:09:50.964143+00
61	UNSOLVED_PYQ	Basic Civil Engineering and Engineering Mechanics - Jun 2022	2022	You are an elite expert AI parser specializing in Engineering Academic exams for RGPV University.\n\nCONTEXT:\nBuilding material for Branch: {branch_name}\nSubject: {subject_code} - {subject_name}\nDocument Type target: {document_type}\n\nYour task is to extract exact information from raw exam papers, syllabi, or notes (provided as text or images) and generate pristine, highly-accurate structured data for them.\nYou MUST output valid JSON conforming strictly to the requested schema.\nCRITICAL INSTRUCTION: DO NOT process or transcribe any Hindi text whatsoever. Extract and process ONLY the English versions of the questions.\nIMAGE INSTRUCTION: If a question or section does NOT contain an image or diagram in the source, set 'image_strategy' to null and 'image_details' to null. DO NOT invent or assume images exist.\nFor 'latex_answer' or any mathematical fields, use Markdown for normal text and wrap ANY math in KaTeX delimiters ($ for inline, $$ for block formulas).	raw_docs/bt-204-basic-civil-engineering-and-engineering-mechanics-jun-2022.pdf	\N	COMPLETED	1	1	0	2	{"questions": [{"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Define workability of the Concrete and discuss the factor that affect the workability of the concrete.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Discuss about the any two-laboratory test conducted on the concrete.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": "A neat sketch of a Dumpy level, showing its main components.", "question_text": "Explain about the description of the Dumpy level with a neat sketch.", "image_strategy": "GEN_PROMPT"}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 6, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Explain in brief with about the different type of levelling operation (Profile, Cross-sectional, Differential and Fly levelling) used in survey of the field.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 8, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "The following are the consecutive reading were taken with a level and a 4-meter levelling staff on a continuously sloping ground at a common interval of $30\\\\,m$. $0.855\\\\left(A\\\\right)$, $1.545$, $2.335$, $3.115$, $3.825$, $0.455$, $1.380$, $2.055$, $2.855$, $3.455$, $0.585$, $1.015$, $1.850$, $2.755$, and $3.845\\\\left(B\\\\right)$. The R.L.of the first reading at A was $380.500$. Make entries in level book and apply the usual check. Determine the gradient of AB. The instrument is shifted after $5^{th}$ and $10^{th}$ reading.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 6, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "An embankment of a width $10\\\\,m$ and side slope of $1.5:1$ is required to be made on a ground which is level in a direction transverse to the centreline. The centre line heights at $40\\\\,m$ intervals area as follows: $0.90$, $1.25$, $2.15$, $2.50$, $1.85$, $1.35$ and $0.85$ Calculate the volume of earth work according to trapezoidal and prismoidal method.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 8, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "The following offset were taken from a line to an irregular boundary line at an interval of $10\\\\,m$ $0$, $2.50$, $3.50$, $5.00$, $4.60$, $3.20$, $0\\\\,m$ Compute the area between the chain line, the irregular boundary line and the end offsets by \\\\begin{enumerate}\\\\item[i)] Mid-Ordinate Rule\\\\item[ii)] Average-Ordinate Rule\\\\item[iii)] The Trapezoidal Rule\\\\item[iv)] Simpson's Rule\\\\end{enumerate}", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 5, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "What are Survey Stations and How to select a Survey Station.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 9, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": "A truss structure with points A, B, C, D, E, F. Point A is a hinge support, point F is a roller support. A vertical load of 50 kN is applied at B, and 30 kN at D. Dimensions: AC = 4m, CE = 4m, EF = 3m. Vertical distance from AC to B is 5m. Vertical distance from CE to D is 4m. The truss forms a triangular shape with a peak at B and D.", "question_text": "Calculate the force in the member shown in fig. using the method of joints.", "image_strategy": "CANVAS", "recreated_image_url": "https://s3.us-east-005.backblazeb2.com/campusprep/recreated/ba6b1456-a83c-4154-88e0-9205a4af5278.png?X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&X-Amz-Credential=005ff988bd983190000000001%2F20260225%2Fus-east-005%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&X-Amz-Date=20260225T191909Z&X-Amz-Expires=3600&X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&X-Amz-Signature=fe251ed7d2b9da5ffd8066d08e7ce1f0bb2ff26878b087fbef05d99a5eeb6411", "recreated_html_source": "<canvas id=\\"canvas\\"></canvas>\\n<script>\\nconst canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');\\nconst ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\\n\\n// Canvas size\\ncanvas.width = 800;\\ncanvas.height = 500;\\n\\n// Styling\\nconst colors = {\\n  member: '#2c3e50',      // slate\\n  support: '#8e44ad',     // indigo\\n  load: '#27ae60',        // emerald\\n  text: '#2c3e50'\\n};\\nctx.lineCap = 'round';\\nctx.font = '16px Arial';\\nctx.textAlign = 'center';\\nctx.textBaseline = 'middle';\\n\\n// Scale (pixels per meter)\\nconst scale = 60;\\n\\n// Logical coordinates (meters)\\nconst points = {\\n  A: {x: 0,   y: 0},\\n  C: {x: 4,   y: 0},\\n  E: {x: 8,   y: 0},\\n  F: {x: 11,  y: 0},\\n  B: {x: 2,   y: -5},   // apex over AC\\n  D: {x: 6,   y: -4}    // apex over CE\\n};\\n\\n// Convert logical to canvas coordinates (origin at bottom‑left with margin)\\nconst margin = 80;\\nfunction toCanvas(pt) {\\n  return {\\n    x: margin + pt.x * scale,\\n    y: canvas.height - margin - pt.y * scale   // y positive upward in logical space\\n  };\\n}\\n\\n// Draw members\\nctx.strokeStyle = colors.member;\\nctx.lineWidth = 3;\\nfunction drawLine(p1, p2) {\\n  const a = toCanvas(p1);\\n  const b = toCanvas(p2);\\n  ctx.beginPath();\\n  ctx.moveTo(a.x, a.y);\\n  ctx.lineTo(b.x, b.y);\\n  ctx.stroke();\\n}\\n\\n// Base line A‑C‑E‑F\\ndrawLine(points.A, points.C);\\ndrawLine(points.C, points.E);\\ndrawLine(points.E, points.F);\\n\\n// Triangles\\ndrawLine(points.A, points.B);\\ndrawLine(points.B, points.C);\\ndrawLine(points.C, points.D);\\ndrawLine(points.D, points.E);\\n\\n// Supports\\nfunction drawHinge(pt) {\\n  const c = toCanvas(pt);\\n  ctx.strokeStyle = colors.support;\\n  ctx.lineWidth = 2;\\n  ctx.beginPath();\\n  ctx.moveTo(c.x - 12, c.y);\\n  ctx.lineTo(c.x + 12, c.y);\\n  ctx.moveTo(c.x - 8, c.y + 6);\\n  ctx.lineTo(c.x + 8, c.y + 6);\\n  ctx.moveTo(c.x - 4, c.y + 12);\\n  ctx.lineTo(c.x + 4, c.y + 12);\\n  ctx.stroke();\\n}\\nfunction drawRoller(pt) {\\n  const c = toCanvas(pt);\\n  ctx.strokeStyle = colors.support;\\n  ctx.lineWidth = 2;\\n  // vertical line\\n  ctx.beginPath();\\n  ctx.moveTo(c.x, c.y);\\n  ctx.lineTo(c.x, c.y - 20);\\n  ctx.stroke();\\n  // two rollers\\n  ctx.beginPath();\\n  ctx.arc(c.x - 6, c.y - 20, 6, 0, Math.PI * 2);\\n  ctx.arc(c.x + 6, c.y - 20, 6, 0, Math.PI * 2);\\n  ctx.stroke();\\n}\\ndrawHinge(points.A);\\ndrawRoller(points.F);\\n\\n// Loads\\nfunction drawLoad(pt, magnitude, label) {\\n  const c = toCanvas(pt);\\n  const length = 40; // arrow length in px\\n  ctx.strokeStyle = colors.load;\\n  ctx.fillStyle = colors.load;\\n  ctx.lineWidth = 2;\\n  ctx.beginPath();\\n  ctx.moveTo(c.x, c.y);\\n  ctx.lineTo(c.x, c.y + length);\\n  ctx.stroke();\\n  // arrowhead\\n  ctx.beginPath();\\n  ctx.moveTo(c.x - 6, c.y + length - 6);\\n  ctx.lineTo(c.x, c.y + length);\\n  ctx.lineTo(c.x + 6, c.y + length - 6);\\n  ctx.fill();\\n  // label\\n  ctx.fillStyle = colors.text;\\n  ctx.fillText(label + ' (' + magnitude + ' kN)', c.x, c.y + length + 15);\\n}\\ndrawLoad(points.B, 50, 'P₁');\\ndrawLoad(points.D, 30, 'P₂');\\n\\n// Point labels\\nfunction labelPoint(name, pt) {\\n  const c = toCanvas(pt);\\n  ctx.fillStyle = colors.text;\\n  ctx.fillText(name, c.x, c.y - 15);\\n}\\n['A','B','C','D','E','F'].forEach(n => labelPoint(n, points[n]));\\n</script>"}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 6, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Find the least value of P required to cause the system of blocks shown in Fig. P-511 to have impending motion to the left. The coefficient of friction under each block is $0.20$.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 8, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": "A truss structure with points A, E, F, D, B, C. Point A is a hinge support, point D is a roller support. A vertical load of 80 kN is applied at C, and 50 kN at F. Dimensions: AE = 1m, EF = 1m, FD = 1m. Vertical distance from AE to B is 0.75m. Vertical distance from EF to C is 0.75m. The truss forms a triangular shape with a peak at B and C.", "question_text": "Determine the force in members BC, CE, and EF shown in fig. using the method of joints.", "image_strategy": "CANVAS", "recreated_image_url": "https://s3.us-east-005.backblazeb2.com/campusprep/recreated/9da410e2-8d29-48f0-ad99-5c88da5fa8a2.png?X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&X-Amz-Credential=005ff988bd983190000000001%2F20260225%2Fus-east-005%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&X-Amz-Date=20260225T191909Z&X-Amz-Expires=3600&X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&X-Amz-Signature=87b55daf6cbb30cdaabff40866b9f2c2b49c5984483251bbdc4d5e9cbed3798f", "recreated_html_source": "<canvas id=\\"canvas\\"></canvas>\\n<script>\\n(() => {\\n  const canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');\\n  const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\\n\\n  // Set up high‑DPI canvas\\n  const dpr = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;\\n  const logicalWidth = 400;   // logical pixels (≈4 m @ 100 px/m)\\n  const logicalHeight = 250;  // enough for vertical members\\n  canvas.style.width = logicalWidth + 'px';\\n  canvas.style.height = logicalHeight + 'px';\\n  canvas.width = logicalWidth * dpr;\\n  canvas.height = logicalHeight * dpr;\\n  ctx.scale(dpr, dpr);\\n\\n  // Styling\\n  const colors = {\\n    member: '#2c3e50',   // slate\\n    support: '#8e44ad',  // indigo\\n    load: '#27ae60',     // emerald\\n    dim: '#7f8c8d'       // gray\\n  };\\n  ctx.lineCap = 'round';\\n  ctx.font = '14px sans-serif';\\n  ctx.textAlign = 'center';\\n  ctx.textBaseline = 'middle';\\n\\n  // Geometry (meters → pixels, 100 px per metre)\\n  const scale = 100;\\n  const A = {x: 0,   y: 0};\\n  const E = {x: 1,   y: 0};\\n  const F = {x: 2,   y: 0};\\n  const D = {x: 3,   y: 0};\\n  const B = {x: 0.5, y: -0.75};\\n  const C = {x: 1.5, y: -0.75};\\n\\n  // Convert to canvas coordinates (origin top‑left, y down)\\n  const toCanvas = p => ({\\n    x: p.x * scale + 50,               // left margin\\n    y: logicalHeight - (p.y * scale) - 30 // bottom margin\\n  });\\n\\n  const pts = {A, B, C, D, E, F};\\n  for (let key in pts) pts[key] = toCanvas(pts[key]);\\n\\n  // Helper to draw a line\\n  const line = (p1, p2, style = colors.member, width = 2) => {\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = style;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = width;\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(p1.x, p1.y);\\n    ctx.lineTo(p2.x, p2.y);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n  };\\n\\n  // Draw members\\n  line(pts.A, pts.B);\\n  line(pts.B, pts.E);\\n  line(pts.E, pts.C);\\n  line(pts.C, pts.F);\\n  line(pts.B, pts.C); // top chord\\n  line(pts.A, pts.E);\\n  line(pts.E, pts.F);\\n  line(pts.F, pts.D);\\n  line(pts.A, pts.D); // optional lower chord for completeness\\n\\n  // Draw supports\\n  const drawHinge = (p) => {\\n    const size = 12;\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = colors.support;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 2;\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(p.x - size, p.y);\\n    ctx.lineTo(p.x + size, p.y);\\n    ctx.lineTo(p.x, p.y - size);\\n    ctx.closePath();\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n  };\\n  const drawRoller = (p) => {\\n    const size = 12;\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = colors.support;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 2;\\n    // vertical line\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(p.x, p.y);\\n    ctx.lineTo(p.x, p.y - size);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n    // rollers (three small circles)\\n    const r = 3;\\n    const spacing = 6;\\n    for (let i = -1; i <= 1; i++) {\\n      ctx.beginPath();\\n      ctx.arc(p.x + i * spacing, p.y - size - r - 2, r, 0, Math.PI * 2);\\n      ctx.stroke();\\n    }\\n  };\\n  drawHinge(pts.A);\\n  drawRoller(pts.D);\\n\\n  // Draw loads\\n  const drawLoad = (p, magnitude, label) => {\\n    const length = 40; // arrow length\\n    const head = 8;\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = colors.load;\\n    ctx.fillStyle = colors.load;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 2;\\n    // vertical arrow (downwards)\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(p.x, p.y);\\n    ctx.lineTo(p.x, p.y + length);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n    // arrowhead\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(p.x - head, p.y + length - head);\\n    ctx.lineTo(p.x, p.y + length);\\n    ctx.lineTo(p.x + head, p.y + length - head);\\n    ctx.fill();\\n    // label\\n    ctx.fillStyle = '#000';\\n    ctx.fillText(`${magnitude} kN`, p.x, p.y + length + 15);\\n  };\\n  drawLoad(pts.C, 80, '80 kN');\\n  drawLoad(pts.F, 50, '50 kN');\\n\\n  // Dimension lines\\n  const dimOffset = 20;\\n  const drawDim = (p1, p2, text, vertical = false) => {\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = colors.dim;\\n    ctx.fillStyle = colors.dim;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 1;\\n    const offset = dimOffset;\\n    if (vertical) {\\n      // vertical dimension (p1 above p2)\\n      const x = p1.x + offset;\\n      ctx.beginPath();\\n      ctx.moveTo(p1.x, p1.y);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x, p1.y);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x, p2.y);\\n      ctx.lineTo(p2.x, p2.y);\\n      ctx.stroke();\\n      // ticks\\n      ctx.beginPath();\\n      ctx.moveTo(x - 5, p1.y);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x + 5, p1.y);\\n      ctx.moveTo(x - 5, p2.y);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x + 5, p2.y);\\n      ctx.stroke();\\n      // text\\n      ctx.save();\\n      ctx.translate(x + 12, (p1.y + p2.y) / 2);\\n      ctx.rotate(-Math.PI / 2);\\n      ctx.fillText(text, 0, 0);\\n      ctx.restore();\\n    } else {\\n      // horizontal dimension\\n      const y = p1.y + offset;\\n      ctx.beginPath();\\n      ctx.moveTo(p1.x, p1.y);\\n      ctx.lineTo(p1.x, y);\\n      ctx.lineTo(p2.x, y);\\n      ctx.lineTo(p2.x, p2.y);\\n      ctx.stroke();\\n      // ticks\\n      ctx.beginPath();\\n      ctx.moveTo(p1.x, y - 5);\\n      ctx.lineTo(p1.x, y + 5);\\n      ctx.moveTo(p2.x, y - 5);\\n      ctx.lineTo(p2.x, y + 5);\\n      ctx.stroke();\\n      // text\\n      ctx.fillText(text, (p1.x + p2.x) / 2, y + 12);\\n    }\\n  };\\n\\n  // AE = 1 m, EF = 1 m, FD = 1 m\\n  drawDim(pts.A, pts.E, '1 m');\\n  drawDim(pts.E, pts.F, '1 m');\\n  drawDim(pts.F, pts.D, '1 m');\\n\\n  // vertical distances\\n  drawDim(pts.A, pts.B, '0.75 m', true);\\n  drawDim(pts.E, pts.C, '0.75 m', true);\\n\\n  // Node labels\\n  const labelNode = (p, name) => {\\n    ctx.fillStyle = '#000';\\n    ctx.fillText(name, p.x, p.y - 12);\\n  };\\n  labelNode(pts.A, 'A');\\n  labelNode(pts.B, 'B');\\n  labelNode(pts.C, 'C');\\n  labelNode(pts.D, 'D');\\n  labelNode(pts.E, 'E');\\n  labelNode(pts.F, 'F');\\n})();\\n</script>"}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 6, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Explain about the Moment of inertia and Radius of Gyration.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 8, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": "Shear Force Diagram and Bending Moment Diagram for a simply supported beam of length L, with a point load W at distance 'a' from the left support and 'b' from the right support (where a+b=L).", "question_text": "Draw the Shear force and Bending moment diagram for the simple supported beam carries a Point load of intensity \\"$W$\\" kN at a distance of \\"$a$\\" from the left supports and at a distance of \\"$b$\\" from the right supports. The total span of length \\"$L$\\" m.", "image_strategy": "GEN_PROMPT"}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 3, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Roofs", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 3, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Curing", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "c", "unit": null, "marks": 4, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Force Diagram and Bow's notations", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "d", "unit": null, "marks": 4, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Concurrent and non-concurrent Co- planner forces", "image_strategy": null}]}	t	NATIVE	f	\N	2026-02-25 16:01:50.145638+00	2026-02-25 17:10:28.052856+00
