strate the efficiency of an algorithm.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": 3, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Write an algorithm to convert infix expression into postfix form using Stack. Also evaluate the given postfix form using stack\\n$$2\\\\,3\\\\,9\\\\,*\\\\,+\\\\,2\\\\,3\\\\,\\\\hat{\\\\,}-\\\\,6\\\\,2\\\\,/\\\\,+$$", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": 3, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Write a program in 'C' to implementation of QUEUE.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": 4, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Show that the maximum number of nodes in a binary tree of height h is $2^{h+1}-1$.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": 2, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "What are sparse matrices? Explain the representation of the Sparse matrix. Also, demonstrate the upper triangle and lower triangular sparse matrices. Suggest a space efficient representation for sparse matrices and determine the address determination formulas for it.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": 2, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Write a note on Compaction, overflow, and Underflow in Array term.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": 5, "marks": 14, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "What is HashMap in data structure? How does HashMap handle collisions? Explain with C or Java.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": 5, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": "Draw a directed graph based on the provided adjacency matrix. The nodes are V0, V1, V2, V3. An edge exists from row node to column node if the value is 1.", "question_text": "Draw the directed graph that corresponds to the following adjacency matrix.\\n\\n| | V₀ | V₁ | V₂ | V₃ |\\n|---|---|---|---|---|\\n| V₀ | 0 | 1 | 1 | 0 |\\n| V₁ | 0 | 0 | 1 | 1 |\\n| V₂ | 0 | 0 | 0 | 1 |\\n| V₃ | 1 | 0 | 0 | 0 |", "image_strategy": "CANVAS", "recreated_image_url": "https://s3.us-east-005.backblazeb2.com/campusprep/recreated/35590a22-f345-4889-8103-6ee6cbbc996b.png?X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&X-Amz-Credential=005ff988bd983190000000001%2F20260225%2Fus-east-005%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&X-Amz-Date=20260225T191823Z&X-Amz-Expires=3600&X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&X-Amz-Signature=809ca25085105c56bd2223dd9f3c124a9983d26212195fcf53c7f63805b7aa6e", "recreated_html_source": "<canvas id=\\"canvas\\" style=\\"width:100%; height:100%; display:block;\\"></canvas>\\n<script>\\nconst canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');\\nconst ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\\n\\n// Adjust canvas for high‑DPI displays and make it fill its container\\nfunction resizeCanvas() {\\n    const dpr = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;\\n    const rect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();\\n    canvas.width = rect.width * dpr;\\n    canvas.height = rect.height * dpr;\\n    ctx.scale(dpr, dpr);\\n}\\nwindow.addEventListener('resize', resizeCanvas);\\nresizeCanvas();\\n\\n// ---------- Data ----------\\nconst nodes = ['V0', 'V1', 'V2', 'V3'];\\n// adjacency matrix (row → column)\\nconst adj = [\\n    [0, 1, 0, 1], // V0 → V1, V3\\n    [0, 0, 1, 0], // V1 → V2\\n    [1, 0, 0, 1], // V2 → V0, V3\\n    [0, 0, 0, 0]  // V3 → (none)\\n];\\n\\n// ---------- Layout ----------\\nconst centerX = canvas.clientWidth / 2;\\nconst centerY = canvas.clientHeight / 2;\\nconst radius = Math.min(centerX, centerY) * 0.6;\\n\\n// Compute node positions on a circle\\nconst positions = nodes.map((_, i) => {\\n    const angle = (2 * Math.PI / nodes.length) * i - Math.PI / 2;\\n    return {\\n        x: centerX + radius * Math.cos(angle),\\n        y: centerY + radius * Math.sin(angle)\\n    };\\n});\\n\\n// ---------- Styling ----------\\nconst nodeRadius = 30;\\nconst nodeFill = '#334155';      // slate‑800\\nconst nodeStroke = '#64748b';    // slate‑400\\nconst edgeColor = '#4f46e5';     // indigo‑600\\nconst textColor = '#f1f5f9';     // slate‑100\\nconst arrowSize = 10;\\n\\n// ---------- Helper: draw arrowhead ----------\\nfunction drawArrowhead(x0, y0, x1, y1) {\\n    const angle = Math.atan2(y1 - y0, x1 - x0);\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(x1, y1);\\n    ctx.lineTo(x1 - arrowSize * Math.cos(angle - Math.PI / 6),\\n               y1 - arrowSize * Math.sin(angle - Math.PI / 6));\\n    ctx.lineTo(x1 - arrowSize * Math.cos(angle + Math.PI / 6),\\n               y1 - arrowSize * Math.sin(angle + Math.PI / 6));\\n    ctx.closePath();\\n    ctx.fillStyle = edgeColor;\\n    ctx.fill();\\n}\\n\\n// ---------- Draw edges ----------\\nctx.lineWidth = 2;\\nctx.strokeStyle = edgeColor;\\nctx.fillStyle = edgeColor;\\n\\nfor (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {\\n    for (let j = 0; j < nodes.length; j++) {\\n        if (adj[i][j] === 1) {\\n            const from = positions[i];\\n            const to   = positions[j];\\n\\n            // Compute unit vector for offsetting start/end at node border\\n            const dx = to.x - from.x;\\n            const dy = to.y - from.y;\\n            const len = Math.hypot(dx, dy);\\n            const ux = dx / len;\\n            const uy = dy / len;\\n\\n            const startX = from.x + ux * nodeRadius;\\n            const startY = from.y + uy * nodeRadius;\\n            const endX   = to.x   - ux * nodeRadius;\\n            const endY   = to.y   - uy * nodeRadius;\\n\\n            // Draw line\\n            ctx.beginPath();\\n            ctx.moveTo(startX, startY);\\n            ctx.lineTo(endX, endY);\\n            ctx.stroke();\\n\\n            // Draw arrowhead\\n            drawArrowhead(startX, startY, endX, endY);\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\\n// ---------- Draw nodes ----------\\nctx.font = '16px sans-serif';\\nctx.textAlign = 'center';\\nctx.textBaseline = 'middle';\\n\\nnodes.forEach((label, idx) => {\\n    const {x, y} = positions[idx];\\n\\n    // Node circle\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.arc(x, y, nodeRadius, 0, 2 * Math.PI);\\n    ctx.fillStyle = nodeFill;\\n    ctx.fill();\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = nodeStroke;\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n\\n    // Label\\n    ctx.fillStyle = textColor;\\n    ctx.fillText(label, x, y);\\n});\\n</script>"}, {"part": "b", "unit": 2, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Explore all types of operations that can be performed on a linked list.", "image_strategy": null}]}	t	NATIVE	f	\N	2026-02-25 16:01:50.146203+00	2026-02-25 17:12:11.444769+00
