 "Write a brief note on: Stress and strain", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b) ii)", "unit": null, "marks": 4, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Write a brief note on: Mohr's circle", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Deduce the total extension of a uniformly tapering rod of diameters d and D over a length of L, when the rod is subjected to an axial load P.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "A steel rod of 3 cm diameter and 5 m length is joined by two grips and the rod is maintained at 95°C. When the temperature falls to 30°C, determine the stress and tensile force applied, if i) no yield occurs at the ends ii) yield at the ends is 0.12 cm. E = 2 x 10⁵ MN/m² and α = 12 x 10⁻⁶/°C.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": "A simply supported beam AB of total length 10m. From A, there is a point load of 60 kN at 2m, a uniformly distributed load of 10 kN/m for 4m (from 2m to 6m), and another point load of 40 kN at 6m. The remaining span is 4m to B. The beam is supported at A and B.", "question_text": "Draw the S.F and B.M diagrams of the beam shown in Figure 1.", "image_strategy": "CANVAS", "recreated_image_url": "https://s3.us-east-005.backblazeb2.com/campusprep/recreated/97e5d83b-ab65-44fb-911d-98717e5e635c.png?X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&X-Amz-Credential=005ff988bd983190000000001%2F20260225%2Fus-east-005%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&X-Amz-Date=20260225T191758Z&X-Amz-Expires=3600&X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&X-Amz-Signature=0ec0349960728097c2a75ff7294bfaadea07f5f9afaf61c1607fa48e9a521057", "recreated_html_source": "<canvas id=\\"canvas\\"></canvas>\\n<script>\\n(function() {\\n  const canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');\\n  const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\\n\\n  // Set canvas size (responsive)\\n  function resizeCanvas() {\\n    const dpr = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;\\n    const width = Math.min(window.innerWidth * 0.95, 900); // max 900 px\\n    const height = 200;\\n    canvas.style.width = width + 'px';\\n    canvas.style.height = height + 'px';\\n    canvas.width = width * dpr;\\n    canvas.height = height * dpr;\\n    ctx.scale(dpr, dpr);\\n    draw();\\n  }\\n\\n  // Main drawing routine\\n  function draw() {\\n    ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);\\n    ctx.font = '14px Arial';\\n    ctx.textAlign = 'center';\\n    ctx.textBaseline = 'middle';\\n\\n    // Colours\\n    const beamColor = '#475569';      // slate-700\\n    const supportColor = '#4f46e5';   // indigo-600\\n    const loadColor = '#10b981';      // emerald-500\\n    const textColor = '#111827';      // gray-900\\n\\n    // Geometry\\n    const margin = 60;\\n    const beamY = 100;\\n    const beamLength = 10; // metres\\n    const pxPerM = (canvas.clientWidth - 2 * margin) / beamLength;\\n\\n    // Draw beam\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = beamColor;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 4;\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(margin, beamY);\\n    ctx.lineTo(margin + beamLength * pxPerM, beamY);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n\\n    // Draw supports (simple triangles)\\n    const supportSize = 20;\\n    ctx.fillStyle = supportColor;\\n    // Support A (left)\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(margin, beamY);\\n    ctx.lineTo(margin - supportSize, beamY + supportSize);\\n    ctx.lineTo(margin + supportSize, beamY + supportSize);\\n    ctx.closePath();\\n    ctx.fill();\\n    // Support B (right)\\n    const rightX = margin + beamLength * pxPerM;\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(rightX, beamY);\\n    ctx.lineTo(rightX - supportSize, beamY + supportSize);\\n    ctx.lineTo(rightX + supportSize, beamY + supportSize);\\n    ctx.closePath();\\n    ctx.fill();\\n\\n    // Helper to draw a vertical arrow (downward)\\n    function drawArrow(x, yTop, length, label) {\\n      ctx.strokeStyle = loadColor;\\n      ctx.fillStyle = loadColor;\\n      ctx.lineWidth = 2;\\n      ctx.beginPath();\\n      ctx.moveTo(x, yTop);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x, yTop + length);\\n      ctx.stroke();\\n      // Arrowhead\\n      const headSize = 6;\\n      ctx.beginPath();\\n      ctx.moveTo(x - headSize, yTop + length - headSize);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x, yTop + length);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x + headSize, yTop + length - headSize);\\n      ctx.fill();\\n      // Label\\n      ctx.fillStyle = textColor;\\n      ctx.fillText(label, x, yTop + length + 15);\\n    }\\n\\n    // Point load 60 kN at 2 m\\n    const p1x = margin + 2 * pxPerM;\\n    drawArrow(p1x, beamY - 30, 30, '60 kN');\\n\\n    // Point load 40 kN at 6 m\\n    const p2x = margin + 6 * pxPerM;\\n    drawArrow(p2x, beamY - 30, 30, '40 kN');\\n\\n    // Uniformly distributed load 10 kN/m from 2 m to 6 m\\n    const udlStart = margin + 2 * pxPerM;\\n    const udlEnd = margin + 6 * pxPerM;\\n    const udlWidth = udlEnd - udlStart;\\n    const udlArrowCount = 5;\\n    const udlSpacing = udlWidth / (udlArrowCount - 1);\\n    const udlLength = 25;\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = loadColor;\\n    ctx.fillStyle = loadColor;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 2;\\n    for (let i = 0; i < udlArrowCount; i++) {\\n      const x = udlStart + i * udlSpacing;\\n      ctx.beginPath();\\n      ctx.moveTo(x, beamY - 30);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x, beamY - 30 + udlLength);\\n      ctx.stroke();\\n      // Arrowhead\\n      const head = 5;\\n      ctx.beginPath();\\n      ctx.moveTo(x - head, beamY - 30 + udlLength - head);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x, beamY - 30 + udlLength);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x + head, beamY - 30 + udlLength - head);\\n      ctx.fill();\\n    }\\n    // UDL label\\n    ctx.fillStyle = textColor;\\n    ctx.fillText('10 kN/m', (udlStart + udlEnd) / 2, beamY - 30 + udlLength + 15);\\n\\n    // Dimension marks\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = '#6b7280'; // gray-500\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 1;\\n    function drawDim(x1, x2, y, txt) {\\n      const arrowSize = 6;\\n      // line\\n      ctx.beginPath();\\n      ctx.moveTo(x1, y);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x2, y);\\n      ctx.stroke();\\n      // left arrow\\n      ctx.beginPath();\\n      ctx.moveTo(x1, y - arrowSize);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x1, y + arrowSize);\\n      ctx.stroke();\\n      // right arrow\\n      ctx.beginPath();\\n      ctx.moveTo(x2, y - arrowSize);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x2, y + arrowSize);\\n      ctx.stroke();\\n      // text\\n      ctx.fillStyle = textColor;\\n      ctx.fillText(txt, (x1 + x2) / 2, y - 12);\\n    }\\n    // 0‑2 m\\n    drawDim(margin, p1x, beamY + 40, '2 m');\\n    // 2‑6 m (UDL length)\\n    drawDim(p1x, p2x, beamY + 40, '4 m');\\n    // 6‑10 m\\n    drawDim(p2x, margin + beamLength * pxPerM, beamY + 40, '4 m');\\n\\n    // Labels A and B\\n    ctx.fillStyle = textColor;\\n    ctx.textAlign = 'right';\\n    ctx.fillText('A', margin - 8, beamY + 5);\\n    ctx.textAlign = 'left';\\n    ctx.fillText('B', margin + beamLength * pxPerM + 8, beamY + 5);\\n  }\\n\\n  // Initial draw and resize handling\\n  window.addEventListener('resize', resizeCanvas);\\n  resizeCanvas();\\n})();\\n</script>"}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Find the SF at left support, if a simply supported beam of span 6 m is subjected to an eccentric point load of 8 kN at", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "A simply supported beam of span L, carrying a point load P at 0.3L from left support. Determine the mid-span displacements and slopes at the supports, using the method of integration.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "A compound cylinder is made by shrinking a cylindrical of external diameter 300 mm and internal diameter of 250 mm over an another cylindrical of external diameter 250 mm and internal diameter 200 mm. The radial pressure at the junction after shrinking is 8 N/mm². Find the final stresses sent up across the section, when the compound cylinder is subjected to an internal fluid pressure of 84.5 N/mm².", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Derive the shear stress formula from fundamentals.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "A 120 mm x 50 mm I-Section is subjected to a shearing force of 10kN. Calculate the shear stress at the neutral axis and at the top of the web. Given I = 220 x 10⁴ mm⁴, Area = 9.4 x 10² mm², web thickness = 3.5 mm and flange thickness = 5.5 mm.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "A hollow steel shaft 3 m long must transmit a torque of 25 kNm. The total angle of twist in this length is not to exceed 2.5° and the allowable shearing stress is 90 MPa. Determine the inside and outside diameter of the shaft if G = 85 GPa.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "A thin spherical vessel 100 mm diameter and 12.5 mm thick is filled with water. More water is pumped in until the pressure reaches 4.2 MPa. How much extra water is required to reach this pressure? Assume E = 210 GPa, γ = 0.25.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": "A beam ABC with a hinge at A, a roller support at B, and a free end at C. The span AB is 9.0 m and BC is 5.0 m. A uniformly distributed load of 10.0 kNm⁻¹ acts over the entire span AB. A point load of 20.0 kN acts at the free end C. The flexural rigidity EI = 10.0 MNm².", "question_text": "Construct shear and bending moment diagrams for the loaded beam shown below in the Figure 2.", "image_strategy": "CANVAS", "recreated_image_url": "https://s3.us-east-005.backblazeb2.com/campusprep/recreated/71326b54-1ce1-4073-922d-1c9e4b2cc771.png?X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&X-Amz-Credential=005ff988bd983190000000001%2F20260225%2Fus-east-005%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&X-Amz-Date=20260225T191757Z&X-Amz-Expires=3600&X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&X-Amz-Signature=7de0b75b67e122430f5382db6260df5ea5cc44d1023154bff246aff995d39942", "recreated_html_source": "<canvas id=\\"canvas\\"></canvas>\\n<script>\\n(() => {\\n  const canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');\\n  const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\\n\\n  // Logical dimensions (meters)\\n  const L_AB = 9.0;\\n  const L_BC = 5.0;\\n  const totalLength = L_AB + L_BC; // 14 m\\n  const beamY = 0; // y=0 is the beam axis in logical coords\\n\\n  // Styling colors\\n  const colors = {\\n    beam: '#374151',      // slate-700\\n    hinge: '#6366F1',     // indigo-500\\n    roller: '#10B981',    // emerald-500\\n    udl: '#4B5563',       // slate-600\\n    pointLoad: '#EF4444', // red-500\\n    text: '#111827'       // slate-900\\n  };\\n\\n  // Canvas size & scaling\\n  function resizeCanvas() {\\n    const dpr = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;\\n    const width = Math.min(window.innerWidth, 800);\\n    const height = 200;\\n    canvas.style.width = width + 'px';\\n    canvas.style.height = height + 'px';\\n    canvas.width = width * dpr;\\n    canvas.height = height * dpr;\\n    ctx.scale(dpr, dpr);\\n    draw();\\n  }\\n\\n  // Convert logical (m) to canvas pixels\\n  const margin = 60; // px left/right margin\\n  const beamPxY = 100; // vertical position of beam axis in px\\n  const scale = (canvas.width / (window.devicePixelRatio || 1) - 2 * margin) / totalLength;\\n\\n  function toPxX(xMeter) {\\n    return margin + xMeter * scale;\\n  }\\n\\n  function draw() {\\n    ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);\\n    ctx.font = '14px Arial';\\n    ctx.textAlign = 'center';\\n    ctx.textBaseline = 'middle';\\n    ctx.lineCap = 'round';\\n    ctx.lineJoin = 'round';\\n\\n    // ---- Draw Beam ----\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = colors.beam;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 4;\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(toPxX(0), beamPxY);\\n    ctx.lineTo(toPxX(totalLength), beamPxY);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n\\n    // ---- Supports ----\\n    // Hinge at A (x=0)\\n    const hingeX = toPxX(0);\\n    const hingeSize = 12;\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = colors.hinge;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 2;\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(hingeX, beamPxY);\\n    ctx.lineTo(hingeX - hingeSize, beamPxY + hingeSize);\\n    ctx.lineTo(hingeX + hingeSize, beamPxY + hingeSize);\\n    ctx.closePath();\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.arc(hingeX, beamPxY + hingeSize + 4, 4, 0, Math.PI * 2);\\n    ctx.fillStyle = colors.hinge;\\n    ctx.fill();\\n\\n    // Roller at B (x = L_AB)\\n    const rollerX = toPxX(L_AB);\\n    const rollerRadius = 8;\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = colors.roller;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 2;\\n    // triangle base\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(rollerX, beamPxY);\\n    ctx.lineTo(rollerX - rollerRadius, beamPxY + rollerRadius);\\n    ctx.lineTo(rollerX + rollerRadius, beamPxY + rollerRadius);\\n    ctx.closePath();\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n    // rollers (two circles)\\n    const rollerOffset = 4;\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.arc(rollerX - 4, beamPxY + rollerRadius + rollerOffset, 4, 0, Math.PI * 2);\\n    ctx.arc(rollerX + 4, beamPxY + rollerRadius + rollerOffset, 4, 0, Math.PI * 2);\\n    ctx.fillStyle = colors.roller;\\n    ctx.fill();\\n\\n    // ---- Uniformly Distributed Load on AB ----\\n    const udlIntensity = 10; // kN/m (just for label)\\n    const udlStartX = toPxX(0);\\n    const udlEndX = toPxX(L_AB);\\n    const udlArrowSpacing = 30; // px\\n    const udlHeight = 30; // px\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = colors.udl;\\n    ctx.fillStyle = colors.udl;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 1.5;\\n    for (let x = udlStartX; x <= udlEndX; x += udlArrowSpacing) {\\n      ctx.beginPath();\\n      ctx.moveTo(x, beamPxY - udlHeight);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x, beamPxY);\\n      ctx.stroke();\\n      // arrowhead\\n      ctx.beginPath();\\n      ctx.moveTo(x - 4, beamPxY - udlHeight + 8);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x, beamPxY - udlHeight);\\n      ctx.lineTo(x + 4, beamPxY - udlHeight + 8);\\n      ctx.fill();\\n    }\\n    // label for UDL\\n    ctx.fillStyle = colors.text;\\n    ctx.fillText(`w = ${udlIntensity} kN/m`, (udlStartX + udlEndX) / 2, beamPxY - udlHeight - 15);\\n\\n    // ---- Point Load at C ----\\n    const pointLoad = 20; // kN\\n    const loadX = toPxX(totalLength);\\n    const loadYTop = beamPxY - 50;\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = colors.pointLoad;\\n    ctx.fillStyle = colors.pointLoad;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 2;\\n    // vertical line\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(loadX, beamPxY);\\n    ctx.lineTo(loadX, loadYTop);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n    // arrowhead\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(loadX - 6, loadYTop + 10);\\n    ctx.lineTo(loadX, loadYTop);\\n    ctx.lineTo(loadX + 6, loadYTop + 10);\\n    ctx.fill();\\n    // label\\n    ctx.fillStyle = colors.text;\\n    ctx.fillText(`P = ${pointLoad} kN`, loadX, loadYTop - 15);\\n\\n    // ---- Dimension Annotations ----\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = colors.text;\\n    ctx.fillStyle = colors.text;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 1;\\n    // AB dimension\\n    const dimY = beamPxY + 40;\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(toPxX(0), dimY);\\n    ctx.lineTo(toPxX(L_AB), dimY);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n    // arrows\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(toPxX(0), dimY - 5);\\n    ctx.lineTo(toPxX(0), dimY + 5);\\n    ctx.moveTo(toPxX(L_AB), dimY - 5);\\n    ctx.lineTo(toPxX(L_AB), dimY + 5);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n    ctx.fillText(`AB = ${L_AB} m`, (toPxX(0) + toPxX(L_AB)) / 2, dimY + 15);\\n    // BC dimension\\n    const dimY2 = beamPxY + 70;\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(toPxX(L_AB), dimY2);\\n    ctx.lineTo(toPxX(totalLength), dimY2);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(toPxX(L_AB), dimY2 - 5);\\n    ctx.lineTo(toPxX(L_AB), dimY2 + 5);\\n    ctx.moveTo(toPxX(totalLength), dimY2 - 5);\\n    ctx.lineTo(toPxX(totalLength), dimY2 + 5);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n    ctx.fillText(`BC = ${L_BC} m`, (toPxX(L_AB) + toPxX(totalLength)) / 2, dimY2 + 15);\\n\\n    // ---- EI annotation ----\\n    ctx.fillText(`EI = 10 MN·m²`, toPxX(totalLength) + 50, beamPxY - 20);\\n  }\\n\\n  window.addEventListener('resize', resizeCanvas);\\n  resizeCanvas();\\n})();\\n</script>"}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Find the maximum deflection and slopes at supports of a simply supported beam of span 'L' subjected to a point", "image_strategy": null}]}	t	NATIVE	f	\N	2026-02-25 16:01:50.146764+00	2026-02-25 17:31:36.324531+00
108	UNSOLVED_PYQ	Strength of Materials - Dec 2023	2023	You are an elite expert AI parser specializing in Engineering Academic exams for RGPV University.\n\nCONTEXT:\nBuilding material for Branch: {branch_name}\nSubject: {subject_code} - {subject_name}\nDocument Type target: {document_type}\n\nYour task is to extract exact information from raw exam papers, syllabi, or notes (provided as text or images) and generate pristine, highly-accurate structured data for them.\nYou MUST output valid JSON conforming strictly to the requested schema.\nCRITICAL INSTRUCTION: DO NOT process or transcribe any Hindi text whatsoever. Extract and process ONLY the English versions of the questions.\nIMAGE INSTRUCTION: If a question or section does NOT contain an image or diagram in the source, set 'image_strategy' to null and 'image_details' to null. DO NOT invent or assume images exist.\nFor 'latex_answer' or any mathematical fields, use Markdown for normal text and wrap ANY math in KaTeX delimiters ($ for inline, $$ for block formulas).	raw_docs/ce-305-strength-of-materials-dec-2023.pdf	\N	COMPLETED	1	1	0	1	{"questions": [{"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 6, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Deduce the relation between the Modulus of Elasticity and Modulus of Rigidity.\\nलोच के मापांक और कठोरता के मॉड्यूलस के बीच संबंध स्थापित करें।", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 8, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "A Load of 175 N falls through a height of 40 mm on to a collar rigidly attached to the lower end of a vertical bar 1.8 m long and of 1.8 cm$^2$ cross-sectional area. The upper end of the bar is fixed. Determine the maximum instantaneous stress induced in the bar. Take E = $2 \\\\times 10^5 \\\\text{ N/mm}^2$.", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Deduce the relation between Shear Force and Bending Moment.\\nअपरूपण बल तथा बंकन आघूर्ण के बीच संबंध स्थापित कीजिए।", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": "Draw an overhanging beam with a uniformly distributed load of 4 kN/m over 6m from point A to B, and a point load of 4 kN at point C, which is 2m from B. Point A is a simple support, point B is a simple support. The beam extends 2m beyond B to C.", "question_text": "An overhanging beam is shown in figure 1. Draw the S.F and B.M\\nचित्र 1 में एक लटकता हुआ बीम दिखाया गया है। S.F और B.M को ड्रा करें।", "image_strategy": "CANVAS", "recreated_image_url": "https://s3.us-east-005.backblazeb2.com/campusprep/recreated/fa355cca-001e-4dca-afe6-79afb06a76cd.png?X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256&X-Amz-Credential=005ff988bd983190000000001%2F20260225%2Fus-east-005%2Fs3%2Faws4_request&X-Amz-Date=20260225T191750Z&X-Amz-Expires=3600&X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host&X-Amz-Signature=36ac58fbe8f4fe30cc525cde305b23f72c77705e3f81f863da50395cc92c5f6c", "recreated_html_source": "<canvas id=\\"canvas\\"></canvas>\\n<script>\\nconst canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');\\nconst ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');\\n\\n// Logical drawing size (in arbitrary units)\\nconst LOGICAL_WIDTH = 500;\\nconst LOGICAL_HEIGHT = 250;\\n\\n// Set canvas size to fill its container while preserving aspect ratio\\nfunction resizeCanvas() {\\n    const parent = canvas.parentNode;\\n    const rect = parent.getBoundingClientRect();\\n    canvas.width = rect.width || LOGICAL_WIDTH;\\n    canvas.height = rect.height || LOGICAL_HEIGHT;\\n    draw();\\n}\\nwindow.addEventListener('resize', resizeCanvas);\\nresizeCanvas();\\n\\nfunction draw() {\\n    // Clear\\n    ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);\\n    // Scaling factors\\n    const sx = canvas.width / LOGICAL_WIDTH;\\n    const sy = canvas.height / LOGICAL_HEIGHT;\\n    ctx.setTransform(sx, 0, 0, sy, 0, 0); // map logical → canvas\\n\\n    // Styling\\n    const beamColor = '#374151'; // slate-700\\n    const loadColor = '#4F46E5'; // indigo-600\\n    const pointLoadColor = '#10B981'; // emerald-500\\n    const textColor = '#111827'; // slate-900\\n    ctx.lineCap = 'round';\\n    ctx.lineJoin = 'round';\\n    ctx.font = '12px sans-serif';\\n    ctx.fillStyle = textColor;\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = beamColor;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 4;\\n\\n    // Geometry (meters → logical pixels, 1 m = 50 px)\\n    const scaleM = 50; // 1 m = 50 logical px\\n    const startX = 80; // left margin\\n    const beamY = 150; // vertical position of beam centre\\n    const A = {x: startX, y: beamY};\\n    const B = {x: A.x + 6 * scaleM, y: beamY};\\n    const C = {x: B.x + 2 * scaleM, y: beamY};\\n\\n    // ---- Beam ----\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(A.x, A.y);\\n    ctx.lineTo(C.x, C.y);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n\\n    // ---- Simple supports (triangles) ----\\n    function drawSimpleSupport(pt) {\\n        const h = 15; // height of triangle\\n        const w = 30; // width of base\\n        ctx.beginPath();\\n        ctx.moveTo(pt.x - w/2, pt.y);\\n        ctx.lineTo(pt.x + w/2, pt.y);\\n        ctx.lineTo(pt.x, pt.y + h);\\n        ctx.closePath();\\n        ctx.fillStyle = beamColor;\\n        ctx.fill();\\n    }\\n    drawSimpleSupport(A);\\n    drawSimpleSupport(B);\\n\\n    // ---- Distributed load on AB ----\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = loadColor;\\n    ctx.fillStyle = loadColor;\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 2;\\n    const arrowSpacing = 0.5 * scaleM; // every 0.5 m\\n    const arrowHeight = 30;\\n    for (let x = A.x + arrowSpacing/2; x <= B.x; x += arrowSpacing) {\\n        ctx.beginPath();\\n        ctx.moveTo(x, beamY - arrowHeight);\\n        ctx.lineTo(x, beamY);\\n        ctx.stroke();\\n        // arrow head\\n        ctx.beginPath();\\n        ctx.moveTo(x - 5, beamY - arrowHeight + 10);\\n        ctx.lineTo(x, beamY - arrowHeight);\\n        ctx.lineTo(x + 5, beamY - arrowHeight + 10);\\n        ctx.fill();\\n    }\\n    // Label for distributed load\\n    ctx.fillStyle = loadColor;\\n    ctx.textAlign = 'center';\\n    ctx.fillText('4 kN/m', (A.x + B.x)/2, beamY - arrowHeight - 10);\\n\\n    // ---- Point load at C ----\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = pointLoadColor;\\n    ctx.fillStyle = pointLoadColor;\\n    const ptLoadHeight = 40;\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(C.x, beamY - ptLoadHeight);\\n    ctx.lineTo(C.x, beamY);\\n    ctx.stroke();\\n    // arrow head\\n    ctx.beginPath();\\n    ctx.moveTo(C.x - 6, beamY - ptLoadHeight + 12);\\n    ctx.lineTo(C.x, beamY - ptLoadHeight);\\n    ctx.lineTo(C.x + 6, beamY - ptLoadHeight + 12);\\n    ctx.fill();\\n    // label\\n    ctx.textAlign = 'center';\\n    ctx.fillText('4 kN', C.x, beamY - ptLoadHeight - 10);\\n\\n    // ---- Dimension lines ----\\n    ctx.strokeStyle = '#6B7280'; // gray-500\\n    ctx.lineWidth = 1;\\n    ctx.setLineDash([4,2]);\\n\\n    function drawDim(p1, p2, offset, label) {\\n        const dir = Math.sign(p2.x - p1.x);\\n        const y = p1.y + offset;\\n        // extension lines\\n        ctx.beginPath();\\n        ctx.moveTo(p1.x, p1.y);\\n        ctx.lineTo(p1.x, y);\\n        ctx.moveTo(p2.x, p2.y);\\n        ctx.lineTo(p2.x, y);\\n        // dimension line\\n        ctx.moveTo(p1.x, y);\\n        ctx.lineTo(p2.x, y);\\n        // arrow heads\\n        const arrowSize = 6;\\n        ctx.moveTo(p1.x, y);\\n        ctx.lineTo(p1.x + dir*arrowSize, y - arrowSize);\\n        ctx.moveTo(p1.x, y);\\n        ctx.lineTo(p1.x + dir*arrowSize, y + arrowSize);\\n        ctx.moveTo(p2.x, y);\\n        ctx.lineTo(p2.x - dir*arrowSize, y - arrowSize);\\n        ctx.moveTo(p2.x, y);\\n        ctx.lineTo(p2.x - dir*arrowSize, y + arrowSize);\\n        ctx.stroke();\\n\\n        // label\\n        ctx.fillStyle = '#111827';\\n        ctx.textAlign = 'center';\\n        ctx.fillText(label, (p1.x + p2.x)/2, y - 8);\\n    }\\n\\n    ctx.setLineDash([]);\\n    drawDim(A, B, 40, '6 m');\\n    drawDim(B, C, 40, '2 m');\\n\\n    // ---- Point labels ----\\n    ctx.fillStyle = textColor;\\n    ctx.textAlign = 'center';\\n    ctx.fillText('A', A.x, A.y + 30);\\n    ctx.fillText('B', B.x, B.y + 30);\\n    ctx.fillText('C', C.x, C.y + 30);\\n}\\n</script>"}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 4, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Write the assumptions made in the theory of simple bending.\\nसरल झुकने के सिद्धांत में की गई धारणाओं को लिखिए।", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 5, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Deduce the section modulus for a hollow circular section of internal diameter 'd' and external diameter 'D'.\\nआंतरिक व्यास 'd' और बाहरी व्यास 'D' के एक खोखले गोलाकार अनुभाग के लिए अनुभाग मॉड्यूलस निकालें।", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "c", "unit": null, "marks": 5, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Prove that the ratio of depth to width of the strongest beam that can be cut-out from a circular log of diameter 'd' is 1.414.\\nसिद्ध कीजिए कि व्यास 'd' के एक वृत्ताकार लट्ठे से काटे जा सकने वाले सबसे मजबूत बीम की गहराई और चौड़ाई का अनुपात 1.414 है।", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 14, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Obtain the expression for shearing stress at a section of a\\n100 मिमी $\\\\times$ 15 मिमी निकला हुआ किनारा और 150 मिमी $\\\\times$ 15 मिमी वेब वाला एक टी-सेक्शन बीम एक खंड पर 10 kN के अपरूपण बल के अधीन है। बीम की गहराई पर अपरूपण प्रतिबल के परिवर्तन को आरेखित करें तथा खंड के अधिकतम अपरूपण प्रतिबल का मान प्राप्त करें।", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 4, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Discuss about moment area theorems.\\nआघूर्ण क्षेत्र प्रमेयों के बारे में चर्चा करें।", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 10, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Find the slope and deflection of simply supported beam of span L, carrying\\ni) a point load P at the centre\\nii) a U.D.L of w kN/m over the entire span\\nusing the moment area method.\\nस्पैन L के केवल समर्थित बीम का ढलान और विक्षेपण ज्ञात कीजिए, जो की निम्नलिखित भार उठाते\\ni) केंद्र में एक बिंदु भार P\\nii) पूरे स्पैन में w kN/m का एक U.D.L,\\nक्षण क्षेत्र विधि का उपयोग करें।", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 6, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "Derive an expression for circumferential stress for a thin spherical shell of internal diameter $d$, wall thickness $t$ and subjected to an internal pressure $p$.\\nआंतरिक व्यास $d$, दीवार की मोटाई $t$, और एक आंतरिक दबाव $p$ के अधीन एक पतली गोलाकार खोल के लिए परिधीय तनाव के लिए एक अभिव्यक्ति प्राप्त करें।", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 8, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "A thin cylindrical shell 90cm long, 20cm internal diameter of metal is 8 mm, and is filled with air and liquid. If the cylinder is additionally pumped with 20 cm$^3$ of liquid, determine:\\ni) Pressure exerted by the liquid on the cylinder\\nii) Induced stress\\nE = $2.1 \\\\times 10^5 \\\\text{ N/mm}^2$ and Poisson's ratio = 0.30.\\nएक पतला बेलनाकार खोल 90 सेमी लंबा, 20सेमी आंतरिक व्यास जिसकी धातु की मोटाई 8 मिमी है, वायुऔरद्रव से भरा होता है। यदि सिलेंडर में अतिरिक्त 20 cm$^3$ द्रव पंप किया जाता है, ज्ञात कीजिए:\\ni) द्रव द्वारा बेलन पर डाला गया दाब और\\nii) प्रेरित हूप तनाव\\nE = $2.1 \\\\times 10^5 \\\\text{ N/mm}^2$ और पॉइजन का अनुपात = 0.30 लें।", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "a", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "A metal bar of 10mm diameter when subjected to a pull of 23.55kN gave and elongation of 0.3mm on a gauge length of 200mm. In a torsion test maximum shear stress of 40.71N/mm$^2$ was measured on a bar of 50mm diameter. The angle of twist measured over a length of 300mm being $0^\\\\circ 21'$. Determine the Poisson's Ratio.\\n10 मिमी व्यास की एक धातु की पट्टी जब 23.55kN के खिंचाव के अधीन होती है और 200 मिमी की गेज लंबाई पर 0.3 मिमी की वृद्धि होती है। मरोड़ परीक्षण में अधिकतम अपरूपण प्रतिबल 40.71N/mm$^2$ को 50mm व्यास की छड़ पर मापा गया। 300 मिमी की लंबाई पर मापा गया मोड़ का कोण $0^\\\\circ 21'$ है। पॉइजन अनुपात निर्धारित करें।", "image_strategy": null}, {"part": "b", "unit": null, "marks": 7, "has_or_choice": false, "image_details": null, "question_text": "What must be the length of a 5mm diameter Aluminium wire so that it can be twisted through 1 complete revolution without exceeding a shear of 42N/mm$^2$. Take. G = 27 GPO.\\n5 मिमी व्यास वाले एल्यूमीनियम तार की लंबाई कितनी होनी चाहिए ताकि इसे 42N/mm$^2$ के अपरूपण से अधिक के बिना 1 पूर्ण क्रांति के माध्यम से घुमाया जा सके। मानो, G = 27 GPO", "image_strategy": null}]}	t	NATIVE	f	\N	2026-02-25 16:01:50.146764+00	2026-02-25 17:31:18.277948+00
